01

Change the statistical caliber

As of 2400 hours on February 12,31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps have reported 52,526 confirmed cases (including 8030 severe cases) , 5,911 discharged cases and 1,367 deaths, a total of 59,804 confirmed cases and 13,435 suspected cases have been reported. A total of 471531 close contacts were traced and 181386 close contacts remained under medical observation.

There were 14,840 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (13,436 in Wuhan) , 802 newly cured cases (538 in Wuhan) , 242 newly dead cases (216 in Wuhan) , 43,455 currently confirmed cases (30,043 in Wuhan) , among which 7,084 were serious cases (5,426 in Wuhan) . There were 3441 cured cases (1915 cases in Wuhan) , 1310 died cases (1036 cases in Wuhan) and 48206 confirmed cases (32994 cases in Wuhan) . There were 1377 new suspected cases (620 in Wuhan) and 9028 suspected cases (4904 in Wuhan) .

With the deepening of the understanding of pneumonia and the accumulation of experience in diagnosis and treatment, and in view of the characteristics of the epidemic in Hubei Province, according to the notification of the COVID-19, "Clinical Diagnosis" has been added to the classification of cases in Hubei Province in the fifth edition of the pilot scheme for diagnosis and treatment of pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection issued by the General Office and the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine of the National Health Commission, so that patients can be early in accordance with the confirmed case of standard treatment.

Under the programme, Hubei Province has recently screened suspected cases from the past and revised the diagnostic results, and new patients are diagnosed according to the new diagnostic classification. Hubei Province will start publishing the number of clinically diagnosed cases as well as the number of confirmed cases from the 12th in accordance with the classification of cases published by other provinces in China.

In an interview, Tong Chaohui, an expert from the Central Guidance Group and Deputy Director of Beijing Chaoyang Hospital, said, when we see doctors and diagnose pneumonia, we can get only thirty per cent of the etiology, the remaining eighty per cent depend on clinical diagnosis. From the point of view of clinical thinking and clinician's clinical path, increasing the diagnosis of clinical cases is beneficial to clinician's judgment of disease.

02

2,600 more from the PLA

The Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China called a meeting on the 12th.

General Secretary Xi Jinping stressed that the current epidemic prevention and control work has reached the most arduous key stage, and we must not relax our focus on epidemic prevention and control, and strengthen the prevention and control of areas where the epidemic is particularly serious or high-risk.

With the approval of President Xi Jinping of the Central Military Commission, the military has sent 2,600 additional medical personnel to support Wuhan in the fight against the epidemic of new pneumonia, following the operating model of the Huoshenshan Hospital in Wuhan, to undertake the tasks of medical treatment for confirmed patients in Wuhan Taikang Tongji Hospital and Guanggu district of Hubei Maternal and Child Health Hospital.

Taikang Tongji Hospital plans to launch 860 beds, Hubei Maternal and Child Health Hospital Guanggu district plans to launch 700 beds. Two hospitals have set up clinical ward, set up infection control, examination, special diagnosis, radiation diagnosis, medicine, sterilization supply, information, medical engineering and other auxiliary departments.

The medical forces drawn from the Army, Navy, Air Force, Rocket Force, strategic support forces, Joint Logistics Support Forces, armed police forces a number of medical units. According to the hospital capacity and construction progress, military medical personnel will be put into support in batches, the first batch of 1,400 troops arrived in Wuhan on the 13th.

So far, the army has sent three batches of more than 4,000 medical staff to support Wuhan to fight the new crown pneumonia epidemic.

In the early morning of the 13th, the Air Force sent out 11 transport planes in three types-20, Il-76 and Yun-9, taking off from seven airports in Urumqi, Shenyang, Xining, Tianjin, Zhangjiakou, Chengdu and Chongqing, media reported, air Transport of military personnel and supplies to Wuhan in support of the Hubei medical team.

At 9:30 am on the 13th, all 11 Air Force transport planes arrived at Wuhan Tianhe Airport. This is the first time China's home-made transport-20 large-scale transport aircraft to participate in non-war military operations, but also the first large-scale air force into a system of active service large-scale transport aircraft to carry out emergency large-scale air missions.

Not only are the active duty soldiers coming, but the veterans'medical team is also coming.

With the approval of the Integrated Coordination Group of the Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council, the Ministry of Veterans Affairs has decided to form a veterans affairs system medical team with a total of 120 members in three groups.

The first 40-member medical team, which was organized by the Department of Veterans Affairs of Jiangxi, Shanxi and Zhejiang provinces, and whose members are all medical personnel from the three provincial veterans'hospitals, gathered in Nanchang on September 9 and received relevant professional training, from the 11th to Hubei Province Military Hospital.

"moving support with Shandong characteristics" has become a hot word on the Internet.

On the 11th, under the leadership of the deputy secretary of the CPC Shandong Provincial Committee and the vice-governor, the ninth medical team set out to aid the cities of Wuhan and Huanggang. In order to ensure the orderly start of work, the Shandong headquarters to Huanggang is unprecedented in scale, a total of 10 working groups, including medical prevention group, Security Group, finance group.

Not only that, Shandong has previously donated more than 2500 tons of vegetables and fruits to Hubei, 16 cities and enterprises have also donated a large number of food, air conditioning, electric heaters, hot patrol cars.

Such a heart-to-heart hard nuclear support has won praise from netizens, and it has earned a beautiful name ——"moving house style support in Shandong Province" .

Thanks don't buy it, local entrepreneurs in Huanggang are taking action.

To express the gratitude of the people of Huanggang to the people of Hunan and Shandong provinces as well as the medical staff of the whole country, the four seasons flower and sea scenic spot in Yingshan County has decided to resume business from 2020 until December 31,2020, hunan, Shandong residents with identity cards, all licensed doctors, nurses to implement a year-round admission free.

It's big enough.

The devotee is to be rewarded.

The Nanjing Government has issued a notice on 10 practical matters for medical personnel going to Hubei, including the possibility of attending school once for their children. Those who enrolled in kindergartens in that year, in accordance with the wishes of their parents, were given priority to attend inclusive and quality kindergartens in the district; those who enrolled in compulsory education schools were included in the policy care targets; and those who took the secondary school entrance examination, refer to the relevant provisions on preferential treatment for the education of the Children of servicemen and give them extra points for admission.

If universities in Hubei and Wuhan give preference to their children, there is nothing wrong with that.

03

A million alumni

On the morning of the 12th, Chen Yixin, deputy head of the Central Steering Group and secretary-general of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, said at a meeting of the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters: "To make a good Battle of Wuhan, we must launch a general offensive. ".

Chen Yixin has been deputy head of the Central Steering Group and has been involved in directing the prevention and control of the epidemic in Wuhan for 4 days. During his four days in Wuhan, he fought day and night, studying, familiarizing, thinking and studying, learning to understand the situation of epidemic prevention and control and related knowledge.

At this meeting, Chen Yixin put forward 20 new judgments and new requirements from the aspects of the current epidemic development trend and phase characteristics, how the headquarters works, the target requirements of the current phase of fighting against the epidemic, and key task initiatives.

Chen Yixin puts forward, want"sickbed waits a person"can not"patient waits a bed", ensure"should collect collect all","clear zero everyday". Want to epidemic situation out of "inflection point" , first to confidence out of "inflection point" . To boost morale, rally the people, the implementation of "three-volume control" : Control Increment, reduce stocks, prevent variables, resolutely play a good epidemic prevention and control resistance. It's all hard core.

The latest is:

1. To mobilize the masses of Wuhan Alumni and Chu Merchants, to mobilize market forces, socialization, to play a good Battle of Wuhan to provide more medical supplies in short supply.

2. The Organization Department of the municipal and District Party committees shall immediately begin to study and deploy the work of "promoting cadres by fire line" .

3. Create a command award, to each advanced work in a timely manner to give awards. The first 6 awards and the Second 3 awards were given for each key work.

This is a typical "new move" . It's a tough game. It's a practical game.

There are two major features, one is praise and promotion. Yesterday's article, I mentioned that Tianjin promoted two, respectively from the deputy bureau to the bureau level, from the Department to the deputy bureau.

Second, Wuhan Alumni from intelligence to rescue the second home, the World Wuhan Alumni to help Wuhan, especially to provide medical supplies.

The creativity of the alumni economy has increased, from hui-han to chu-han (Chen Yixin organized a group of Wuhan Alumni to invest in Hinggan League, Inner Mongolia) to hu-han.

It is suggested that alumni from Wuhan should be extended to alumni from all over the province. Medical resources in all cities are tight. More than 140 university alumni associations in the province should take action. For example, Yichang needs the help of the China Three Gorges University Alumni Association.

In 2017, under the guidance of Secretary Chen Yixin and since the founding of the Association of Alumni Associations of Han universities, the strategic cooperation between universities and enterprises in Wuhan has continued to deepen and expand. The new model of "dual recruitment and dual attraction" was initiated nationwide, firing the first shot at the alumni economy in the new era It has issued a work plan for innovating the new model for the economic development of alumni, and held more than 20 educational and intellectual activities for alumni, including special local, overseas and university events, bringing in nearly 100 high-level talents from home and abroad, the total amount of contracts signed for the project has exceeded 2 trillion yuan.

In 2019, Wuhan continued to implement the new concept of "university + " development, with the goal of achieving win-win results through joint efforts, with the focus on strengthening the position of the alliance as the pivot, and deepening the "project to bring millions of alumni wisdom back to the Han people" , expanding the concentric circle of "Wuhan + universities + alumni" and striving to build an upgraded version of the alumni economy of Wuhan in the new era.

The alumni economy has played a new role in the new cap war.

On the 12th, the new Zhangwan District Zhangwan District Zhangwan District epidemic prevention and Control Command issued the 27th circular, announced that Zhangwan District from the 12th 24:00 implementation of wartime control, control measures in principle to 14-day cycle, depending on the city and Zhangwan District epidemic prevention and control effect to be lifted in advance or continued implementation.

This is the first time in the country. It is based on the law on penalties for Public Security Administration, the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases and the regulations on emergency response to public health emergencies. It shows that the cadres in Zhangwan District are bold and bold.

The most important measure is: All buildings will be completely closed, all residents, including non-medical personnel, medical personnel, anti-epidemic civil servants, and employees engaged in basic livelihood protection such as water, electricity, oil and gas, communication networks, grain and vegetables, shall not be allowed to enter or leave the buildings.

Than Wuhan's "three days a person" out more strictly.

04

Focus on the kids, the chickens, the dogs

The infant and Child Products Association of Hubei Province Appeals to me:

The city gate is locked, the village is cut off, the logistics is not enough, the stock is running low, the baby is starving and crying loudly... the young parents are risking their lives for their children's "rations" , each showing their magical powers, into the battle of the rations for our children.

Under the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, the national emergency is not only face masks, protective clothing, goggles and disinfectants and other anti-epidemic materials, but also affects the nerves of millions of families of infant formula.

Since January 23,2020, Wuhan took the lead in the city control measures, infant milk powder has been the most scarce resources for baby parents.

Goods from other places can not come in, they turn to the entity store to snap up, but found that most of the entity mother and child stores have been on holiday. Many large shopping malls closed, some supermarkets on the mother-and-child shelves of milk powder, like meat in short supply, has been cleaned up. Individual mother and baby shop owners open the door, personally battle, empty the store inventory, but found that to purchase, more difficult than the sky!

Hubei Province Baby Products Association related person in charge, upstream many milk enterprises not have no production capacity, but logistics shutdown, resulting in stock can not be sent out. In addition, many workers can not return home for the New Year because of road closures, dairy enterprises and supporting enterprises can not start, production packaging materials can not supply, multiple factors, leading to the entire supply chain broken.

In some places, there have even been reports of young parents who were trapped because their children had no food and were in a desperate situation. They kept dialing 110 numbers until the police finally came to escort them to buy milk powder

Young parents make their own diapers at home.

Mother and baby industry practitioners are also the most beautiful "retrograde" in the fight against the epidemic. After the disaster, mother-and-baby enterprises joined the ranks of donors to bring various kinds of goods and materials in short supply to the areas where the epidemic was serious; many mother-and-baby shops persisted in keeping open, eager to buy baby necessities consumers can see the store that a beam of warm lights; many store staff overcome all kinds of difficulties, in traffic constraints, pedal three rounds, or even walk home, to ensure that the Children's food rations; Both brands, agents, retailers are actively looking for ways to ensure the supply of goods..

Therefore, the Association has entrusted me with a proposal. This is my 19th suggestion during the period of NCP, which has been submitted through the Wechat APP "client of the State Council" , the provincial Minjin, the central committee of the Minjin, and the provincial CPPCC:

Due to the closing of some shops, not only the supplies for adults are tight, but also the supplies for small people are tight. The Hubei Mother and Child Association recommends:

As a positive reflection, it arouses the attention of the whole society. Baby articles (especially milk powder products) should be listed in people's livelihood materials as soon as possible, and relevant measures should be put in place to ensure the smooth flow of mother and baby articles.

Strict safeguards are in place for mother and baby stores and clerks who are able to operate and deliver goods to their doors. Only when the risk of infection is reduced can the supply of goods and materials be sustained, and the society will not be disturbed by doing bad things with good intentions.

Under the guidance of professionals, consumers in the flood-stricken areas treasure the logistics resources and epidemic prevention resources that the government and the whole society squeeze out for just-needed products for mothers and babies, reducing the risk of infection among workers. In Times of emergency, consumers are advised not to overstock.

In other areas of Florida, where the epidemic is not severe, due to the ease of logistics and distribution, young parents should be alert to the risk of cutting off food for their babies.

And the chickens and the ducks are fed.

As of the 11th, there were 12,133 large-scale pig farms in Hubei Province, with 9.27 million pigs kept in pens. There were 11,138 large-scale poultry farms with 149.26 million cage layers and 36.68 million cage broilers.

Due to the severe situation of epidemic prevention and control of NCP, strict traffic control has been implemented in various places, and the normal production and transportation of life-related materials in some breeding enterprises have also been restricted.

Hubei Province agricultural departments actively strengthen communication and coordination and overall planning, to ensure the smooth flow of urgently needed materials, such as feed, to help feed enterprises resume production and work. At present, 384 feed enterprises in the province have more than 70 resume work, can supply 19,520 tons of feed per day.

The province's 312 pig slaughter enterprises, 133 poultry slaughter sites, is gradually resuming production.

The Wuhan Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to small animals is also going against the grain.

Some of the small animals left unattended in the city face the threat of water, food, and even death. The Wuhan Humane Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to animals launched a rescue plan more than half a month ago.

As of December 12, the association through online and offline, mutual help and other channels, the association has received more than 4,200 related help. More than 1,400 visits were made by 68 volunteers and staff members to provide food and water for the animals. In addition, they completed the rescue of small animals in more than 2800 households through QQ groups, wechat groups and so on. The nearly 5,000 animals rescued included cats, dogs, pigs, rabbits, snakes, birds, fish, hamsters and Chinchillas.

Seven pet-related businesses have offered to help with cat and dog food and other supplies, the Wuhan Small Animal Protection Association said Monday on its wechat account.

05

Summary

The medical staff is growing, and there are about 25,000 foreign medical staff.

The leadership is gaining strength, and cadres are being encouraged to take the front line.

To play the role of alumni and Chu Business "love Wuhan" , the rise of a new upsurge in global procurement.

Or as Chen Yixin, deputy team leader, put it best: to launch the general offensive of the Battle of Wuhan.

In this way, the people will be relieved.
